"{\"uid\": \"en.tempo.co-read-1901202-eko-yuli-irawan-apologizes-for-medal-less-paris-olympics-performance\", \"text\": \"Translator  Dewi Elvia Muthiariny  Editor  Petir Garda Bhwana  August 8, 2024 | 07:47 am  TEMPO.CO,Jakarta-Indonesian weightlifting stalwartEko Yuli Irawanextended a public apology and expressed disappointment after failing to clinch a medal at the 2024Paris Olympicsin the 61 kg category on Wednesday, August 7.  \\\"I apologize to the Indonesian people for being unable to present a medal. But I gave it my all,\\\" Eko said in a press release from the Indonesian Olympic Committee (KOI) received in Jakarta on Wednesday.  Eko struggled during the snatch attempts. He successfully lifted 135 kg on the second attempt but failed in the first and third (139 kg). His clean and jerk attempts of 162 kg were also unsuccessful. He even fell in the final failed lift and had discomfort in his right thigh.  Eko attributed his subpar performance to a lingering leg injury. \\\"[I have had] knee issues since last year, and also my right thigh [has been injured] for the past month,\\\" he explained.  Indonesian team doctor Andhika Raspati clarified that the injury was not severe and that he could walk despite limping after the competition. \\\"His condition is not that bad, he can still walk,\\\" he said.  Indonesian Chef de Mission (CdM) Responds  The Chef de Mission (CdM) of the Indonesian contingent, Anindya Bakrie, lauded Eko's efforts and acknowledged his apology. \\\"We witnessed his determination. Eko is a veteran athlete who competed against younger opponents. We appreciate his participation in his fifth Olympics,\\\" she said.  Eko Yuli Irawan is a four-time Olympian. The weightlifter who was born in Lampung previously earned a bronze medal at the 2008 Beijing Olympics, followed by another bronze in the 2012 London Olympics. He claimed silver at the 2016 Rio de Janeiro Olympics and repeated the achievement in the 2020 Tokyo Olympics.  In the 2024 Paris Olympics, the gold medal in the men's 61 kg category went to China's Li Fabin with a total lift of 310 kg, followed by Thailand's Theerapong Silachai in second and the United States' Morris Hampton in third.  ANTARA  Editor's Choice:5 Interesting Facts About Boy Pohan, Paris 2024 Olympics Boxing Referee from Indonesia  Click hereto\\u00a0get\\u00a0the latest news updates from Tempo on Google News  Recommended  World Cup 2026 Draw: Trump, Infantino and a Peace Prize  3 hours ago  10 Best World Cup Finals: The Most Memorable Matches in Football History  6 hours ago  Indonesia U-23 SEA Games 2025 Schedule: Philippines Await in Opener  1 days ago  Top 10 Best Football Managers in Europe in 25/26 Season  2 days ago  10 Oldest Players in World Cup History  3 days ago  2025 Thailand SEA Games Update: 11 Sports Venues Moved Due to Floods  4 days ago  Indonesia Unveils U-23 SEA Games Squad Featuring Four Diaspora Players  4 days ago  Flooding Forces Thailand to Move 10 SEA Games Sports to Bangkok  5 days ago  Indonesia Forward Hokky Caraka Aims to Settle Personal 'Debt' at SEA Games 2025  5 days ago  U-23 Indonesia Team Departs for Thailand on Friday for 2025 SEA Games  5 days ago  Indonesia Secures 10th Spot in Paris 2024 Olympics with Weightlifting Athlete Eko Yuli Irawan  4 April 2024  Indonesia continues to secure spots in the Paris 2024 Olympics.  Olympic Medalist Eko Yuli Irawan Fails to Win Medal in Asian Games  2 Oktober 2023  Indonesian lifter Eko Yuli Irawan failed to bring home any medals at this year's Asian Games in Hangzhou, China.  Popular  KPK Summons Ridwan Kamil in Bank BJB Ad Graft Case  15 hours ago  Today's Top 3 News: Prabowo Departs for Sumatra, 10 Best Places to Retire in US 2026  7 hours ago  Sumatra Floods: Civil Groups, Lawmakers Urge National Disaster Status  17 hours ago  PLN Ensures Swift Repair of Electrical Network Damaged by Aceh Flood  14 hours ago  BMKG Forecasts Afternoon Rain Across Most of Jakarta  19 hours ago  Major Routes in Aceh Still Cu